<h1 class="Article-title">Installation</h1>
<p class="Text--lead">How to get the files from github, install all the npm modules and build Atomic for the first time</p>

<h2>Requirements</h2>

<p>
Requires at least version 6 of Node. We reccomend using <a href="https://github.com/creationix/nvm" target="blank">nvm</a> to install and manage
your Node versions.</p>

<h2>Installation</h2>

<p>Clone from github, install node modules and run atomic.</p>

<div class="docs-code docs-code--cmd">
<pre><code>git clone https://github.com/jaywing/atomic.git MyApp
cd MyApp
yarn add blendid
yarn start
</code></pre>
</div>

<h3>Starting a fresh project</h3>

<p>If you plan on using this to start a new project, be sure and clear out the git data start a fresh history:</p>

<div class="docs-code docs-code--cmd">
<pre><code>rm -rf .git && git init
git commit -m "Initialised with Atomic"
</code></pre>
</div>

